# ThruHike Content API

The ThruHike Content API is a simple API allowing users to access data about
long distance walking routes in the UK, along with map data.

# Group Routes

Resources related to routes in the API.

## List Routes [/routes]

### Get Routes [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (array[Route])

+ Response 500 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ErrorInternalServerError)

## Get Route [/routes/{id}]

### Get Route [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Route)

+ Response 400 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ErrorInvalidRouteID)
+ Response 404 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ErrorRouteNotFound)
+ Response 500 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ErrorInternalServerError)

+ Parameters
    + id: `pennine-way` (string) - ID of the Route, in kebab case (a-z)

## Get Route Map Data [/routes/{id}/data{?format}]

### Get Route Map Data [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    ```
    {
        "type": "FeatureCollection",
        "features": [
            {
            "type": "Feature",
            "geometry": {
                "type": "LineString",
                "coordinates": [
                    [0.061695378, 51.4986717807],
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
    ```

+ Response 200 (application/gpx+xml)

+ Response 400 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ErrorInvalidRouteID)
+ Response 404 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ErrorRouteNotFound)
+ Response 500 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ErrorInternalServerError)

+ Parameters
    + id: `pennine-way` (string) - ID of the Route, in kebab case (a-z)
    + format (enum[string], optional) - Format of the map data
        + Default: geojson
        + Members
            + geojson
            + gpx
            + mapbox

## Data Structures

### Author (object)

+ name: `Ramblers: Pennine Way` (required, string) - Author of the route guide
+ url: `https://www.ramblers.org.uk/go-walking/routes-and-places-to-walk/paths-index/national-trail/pennine-way.aspx`
  (required, string) - URL of the route guide

### Distance (object)

+ kilometers: 429 (required, number) - Total distance of route in kilometers
+ miles: 268 (required, number) - Total distance of route in miles

### ErrorInternalServerError (object)

+ code: 500 (required, number)
+ error: Internal server error occured (required, string)

### ErrorInvalidRouteID (object)

+ code: 400 (required, number)
+ error: `Route ID must be kebab case (a-z)` (required, string)

### ErrorRouteNotFound (object)

+ code: 404 (required, number)
+ error: Route not found (required, string)

### Route (object)

+ title: Pennine Way (required, string) - Name of route
+ imageURI: `https://via.placeholder.com/400x200` (required, string) - Static
  image of the route
+ duration: 16 (required, number) - Total duration of the route, in days
+ distance (required, Distance)
+ guides (required, array[Author])
+ summary (required, array[Summary])

### Summary (object)

+ author (required, Author)
+ text: `The Pennine Way is the oldest, and arguably the most iconic, of Englandâ€™s National Trails.`
  (required, string) - Route summary
